SIMPLE: overdo
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Overdo
<hw>O`ver*do"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp.</pos> <conjf>Overdid</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Overdone</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Overdoing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To do too
much; to exceed what is proper or true in doing; to exaggerate; to carry
too far.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Anything so <qex>overdone</qex> is from the purpose of
playing.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To overtask. or overtax; to fatigue; to exhaust;
<as>as, to <ex>overdo</ex> one's strength</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To surpass; to excel.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Tennyson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To cook too much; <as>as, to <ex>overdo</ex> the
meat</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overdo</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Overdo
<hw>O`ver*do"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To labor too hard; to do too
much.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Overdoer</ent>⟦br⟧
